
[1]grievousness

   GRIE'VOUSNESS, n. Oppressiveness; weight that gives pain or distress;
   as the grievousness of a burden.

   1. Pain; affliction; calamity; distress; as the grievousness of
   sickness, war or famine.

   2. Greatness; enormity; atrociousness; as the grievousness of sin or
   offenses.
